<body style="text-align: center;">
  <div style="margin: 0px auto;padding: 0px; width: 524px; text-align: left;">
    <p style="border: 0; margin: 0;"><img alt="Everything but the Chef Weekly Reminder" src="http://ebtchef.com/images/emails/weekly/everything_but_the_chef.png" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;" /><a href="http://ebtchef.com/ect?s=<%=@user.id%>&e=<%=@email_id%>&next=<%=u "http://ebtchef.com/member"%>"><img alt="Login to my account" src="http://ebtchef.com/images/emails/weekly/login_to_my_account.png" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;" /></a></p>
    <p style="border: 0; margin: 0;"><img alt="Simply delicious meals you can make" src="http://ebtchef.com/images/emails/weekly/delicious_meals.png" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;" /></p>
    <div style="border-right: 1px solid #d7c59f; border-left: 1px solid #d7c59f; border-bottom: 1px solid #d7c59f; color: #808080; font-family: arial, verdana, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: .8em;margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px; width: 522px;">
      <div style="padding: 15px 40px; color: #333; background-color: #fff; word-spacing: .25em; line-height: 1.3em;">
  	    <p style="font: 12px arial; color: #333;">Hello <%= @user.first_name %>,</p>
    	  <p style="font: bold 12px arial; color: #45616c;">We are happy to notify you that this week's meal plans brought to you by <em>Everything but the Chef</em> are ready at <a href="http://ebtchef.com/ect?s=<%=@user.id%>&e=<%=@email_id%>&next=<%=u "https://ebtchef.com/member"%>" style="color: #45616c;">EbtChef.com</a></p>
    	  <p style="font: 12px arial; color: #333;">To learn how to get Chef's service completely <em style="font: bold 15px arial; color: #333;">FREE</em> <a href="http://ebtchef.com/ect?s=<%=@user.id%>&e=<%=@email_id%>&next=<%=u "http://ebtchef.com/member/main/viral"%>" style="color: 5c020a;">click here!</a></p>

    	   <!-- Begin content -->
    	  <em style="font: bold italic 15px arial; color: #5c020a;">This Week's Tip: </em>
        <!-- Tip -->
    	  <p style="font: bold 12px arial; color: #333;">
          <p>Grab It Easily</p>
        </p>

          <p>When you get a splinter try scotch tape, or other sticky variety before tweezers or a needle. Put the tape over the splinter and pull. This will painlessly and easily remove many splinters</p>

          <p>For More great tips to enrich family life visit our website!</p>
          <!-- treat -->
    	  <p style="font: bold italic 15px arial; color: #5c020a;">Treat Your Family Recipe</p>
        
    	  <ul style="list-style: none; margin: 0px 0;">
    	    <li style="font: bold 12px arial; color: #333;">Peanut Butter Ice Cream Pie<li>
            <li><br /></li>
    	      <li>4-5 cups vanilla ice cream, softened</li>
    	      <li>1/3 cup peanut butter</li>
    	      <li>2/3 cup butterscotch chips</li>
    	      <li>2/3 cup milk chocolate chips</li>
    	      <li>1, 9 inch graham cracker crust</li>
    	      
  	  </ul>
    	      <p>Take ice cream out of freezer and let sit to soften while you melt peanut butter, and chips in a double boiler (or microwave). Pour 1/2 melted mixture in bottom of crust. Add soft ice cream and top with remaining melted mixture. Keep in freezer (covered after top shell hardens)</p>	  
    	  <br/>
        <!-- email of the week -->
        <em style="font: bold italic 15px arial; color: #5c020a;">Chef Email of the Week</em>
        <!-- from -->
        <p style="font: 12px arial; color: #333;">Question/Comment from a Chef customer:</p>
        <!-- question -->
        <p style="font: 12px arial; color: #333;">Thank you for responding so quickly... My original email was kind of unclear. In my favorites, it has a list of the dishes but the recipe is not shown. What do I need to do to see the recipe?</p>
        <p>Stephanie</p>
        <!-- response -->
        <p style="font: bold italic 15px arial; color: #5c020a;">Chef response:</p>
        <p>Hi Stephanie,</p>
        <p>Good question. Chef is designed to allow customers to add to and delete recipes from their meal plans, so the way you get the recipe to show up from your favorites file is to add it to a meal plan. Then you can copy and paste that particular recipe to a word doc and print that out or just print the entire meal plans page. Of course, if you don't want the recipe in the meal plans once you've printed it, you can easily delete it from your meal plan page.</p>
        <p>You have brought up a good point...we may need to consider changing some things.</p>
        
        
        
        <p style="font: 12px arial; color: #45616c;">Thanks! Please remember to tell all your friends about Chef service, and have a great day!</p>
        <p style="font: italic 15px arial; color: #5c020a;"><i>Chef</i></p>
